  "prompt": "What is 3E - 3 tier AC in Duronto?",
  "response": "In the context of Indian Railways, \"3E\" stands for the \"3rd AC Economy\" class, which is a type of air-conditioned accommodation available on some trains, including Duronto Express. The 3rd AC Economy class is similar to the standard 3rd AC (3A) class but is designed to be more economical. This class generally features:\n\n- Air-conditioned coaches with sleeping berths arranged in tiers (bunks).\n- The berths are arranged in three tiers on either side of the compartment and two tiers on the aisle side.\n- Bedding is typically provided as part of the ticket price.\n- The amenities might be slightly more basic compared to regular 3rd AC, with differences in berth materials or the number of berths per compartment.\n\nDuronto Express trains are a series of long-distance, high-speed trains operated by Indian Railways, designed to connect major cities with minimal stops in between. The addition of 3E class in Duronto trains offers passengers an affordable, comfortable air-conditioned travel option.",
